      "writtenOn": "2019-04-23T02:49:40Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "i take it that this is used to catch panics if w.fin is closed when L60 writes to it -- is that correct? i wonder if there\u0027s a better way to do this. maybe also use a mutex and bool to make sure it\u0027s only closed once?\n\nw.mutex.Lock()\ndefer w.mutex.Unlock()\nif !w.stopped {\n    w.fin \u003c- struct{}{}\n    w.stopped \u003d true\n}",
      "revId": "b63d161c96fd3413768f0a7b5faa98cfcefac60a",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
